comment:
Would be a three, but at the price, definitely a four. 
Bonus of vanilla and caramel without cinnamon
Sweet vanilla nose. Sweet oak flavor & finish. Mild alcohol lingering flavor with sweet oak flavors. Recommend to anyone that wants a very simple bourbon.

I get a faint caramel scent on the nose. Body had an incredibly sweet mouth feel, almost like a scotch. The only flavors I can pick out are syrup and powdered sugar. Finish turns into alternating flavors of cinnamon and cherry. That cherry runoff is delicious.

This tastes like breakfast.

No. 
This smells & tastes like stale cereal. It legitimately reminded me of Kix cereal and not in a good way.
A pretty standard bourbon. Obviously sourced though not as apparent on the label as it should be. I look forward to real or more interesting releases from this company.

When I bought this bourbon I thought it was Texas bourbon. I am confused about it’s real origin. I felt it is no sincere to label it as Texas bourbon that actually made in Tennessee. Regardless it is relative smooth, sweet, a typical bourbon.
Pallet: Vanilla, maple, low burn, smooth finish. Great sipping bourbon, prefer on rocks
A little caramel scent on the nose. Taste had a pleasant sweet mouth feel. I pick up caramel and powdered sugar. Finish is mild cinnamon and cherry.  Very mild pour but delicious easy drinker.
It is balanced with features a great bourbon, sweet and smooth. I was a little hush on as I wasn’t clear the real origin.
Smooth, little to no bite. Slightly sweet with the classic bourbon notes of vanilla and some oaky-ness. Not very distinctive, but a pleasant and easy drink.
